DTSTART:20260402T210000Z
DTEND:20260402T220000Z
LOCATION:SIDNEY AND LOIS ESKENAZI MUSEUM OF ART - Room Number: Featured E
 xhibitions Gallery\, First Floor
SUMMARY:Drop-in Tours and Crafting
DESCRIPTION:An Immersive ExperienceInspired by Indonesia's spectacular co
 ral reefs\, acclaimed fiber artist Mulyana (b. 1984\, Bandung\, Indonesia
 ) invites you to wander through a handcrafted seascape where art and ecol
 ogy meet.  Explore colorful coral reefs\, playful fish\, and fantastical 
 sea creatures ŌĆö all meticulously hand-knit and crocheted.  Pause to ref
 lect on the delicate balance between human wellbeing and the vitality of 
 our oceans.  Chat with a Museum Guide to deepen your understanding.  Crea
 te Your Own Sea CreatureEnjoy a hands-on activity in the gallery.  No pri
 or experience is needed ŌĆö a volunteer can guide you step by step.  Choo
 se from a fish\, octopus\, lobster\, sea urchin\, or crab.  All supplies 
 are provided\, so you can dive right in!  Why Visit? This exhibition is m
 ore than art ŌĆö it's a living conversation about beauty\, fragility\, an
 d our shared responsibility to protect the ocean. Whether you're an art l
 over\, a family looking for a creative activity\, or simply curious\, Vit
 al Ecosystems offers a memorable experience for all ages.
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<h4><strong>An Immersive Experience</strong>
 </h4><ul><li>Inspired by Indonesia's spectacular coral reefs\, acclaimed 
 fiber artist Mulyana (b. 1984\, Bandung\, Indonesia) invites you to wande
 r through a handcrafted seascape where art and ecology meet.  </li><li>Ex
 plore colorful coral reefs\, playful fish\, and fantastical sea creatures
  ŌĆö all meticulously hand-knit and crocheted.  </li><li>Pause to reflect
  on the delicate balance between human wellbeing and the vitality of our 
 oceans.  </li><li>Chat with a Museum Guide to deepen your understanding. 
  </li></ul><h4><strong>Create Your Own Sea Creature</strong></h4><ul><li>
 Enjoy a hands-on activity in the gallery.  </li><li>No prior experience i
 s needed ŌĆö a volunteer can guide you step by step.  </li><li>Choose fro
 m a fish\, octopus\, lobster\, sea urchin\, or crab.  </li><li>All suppli
 es are provided\, so you can dive right in!  </li></ul><p><strong>Why Vis
 it?</strong> This exhibition is more than art ŌĆö it's a living conversat
 ion about beauty\, fragility\, and our shared responsibility to protect t
 he ocean. Whether you're an art lover\, a family looking for a creative a
 ctivity\, or simply curious\, <em>Vital Ecosystems</em> offers a memorabl
 e experience for all ages.</p>
