LOCATION:SIDNEY AND LOIS ESKENAZI MUSEUM OF ART - Room Number: Check in w
 ith Guest Services on the first floor
SUMMARY:Curator-led Tour
DESCRIPTION:Step into the world of acclaimed photographer Rania Matar (b.
  1964\, Lebanon)\, whose striking portraits document young women persisti
 ng in uncertain times. Matar's lens highlights women's creativity\, stren
 gth\, dignity\, and resilienceŌĆöoffering a powerful counter-narrative to
  the challenges of her country and region. Read more about this featured 
 exhibition (https://artmuseum.indiana.edu/exhibitions/upcoming/_feature-e
 xhibitions/2026-03-05-rania-matar-where-do-i-go.html).  Join us for a rar
 e opportunity to explore the artist's work in depth\, guided by the schol
 ar who researched and curated the exhibition. Read Leila Reichert's bio. 
 (http://Elliot%20Josephine%20Leila%20Reichert%20is%20an%20American%20cura
 tor\,%20critic\,%20and%20editor.%20She%20is%20the%20inaugural%20Curator%2
 0of%20Contemporary%20Art%20at%20the%20Eskenazi%20Museum%20of%20Art%20at%2
 0Indiana%20University%20and%20was%20a%202023-24%20Propel%20Fellow%20with%
 20the%20Association%20of%20Art%20Museum%20Curators%20Foundation.%20She%20
 was%20formerly%20Art%20Editor%20of%20Newcity%20and%20Assistant%20Curator%
 20at%20the%20Block%20Museum%20of%20Art\,%20Northwestern%20University.%20S
 he%20has%20curated%20and%20assisted%20in%20developing%20critically%20cele
 brated%20exhibitions%20in%20the%20United%20States%20and%20abroad.%20Her%2
 0critical%20writing%20has%20been%20published%20in%20the%20Journal%20of%20
 Visual%20Studies\,%20Hyperallergic\,%20the%20Brooklyn%20Rail\,%20Newcity%
 20Art\,%20and%20The%20Seen\,%20among%20others.%20She%20holds%20dual%20mas
 ters%E2%80%99%20degrees%20in%20Modern%20and%20Contemporary%20Art%20Histor
 y%20and%20Arts%20Administration%20and%20Cultural%20Policy%20from%20the%20
 School%20of%20the%20Art%20Institute%20of%20Chicago%20and%20a%20Bachelors%
 20of%20Arts%20with%20Honors%20in%20Art%20History%20from%20Northwestern%20
 University\,%20where%20she%20graduated%20summa%20cum%20laude.)  Reserve y
 our spot today for a chance to connect with Rania Matar's striking photog
 raphs in a personal\, meaningful way. Leila will share the stories\, rese
 arch\, and insights behind the exhibition\, making this experience as mem
 orable as the photography itself.  &#160\;Know Before You GoSpace is limi
 ted to 15 participants. RSVP to reserve a space. Walk-ins are welcome if 
 space is available. If this page says "registration has closed"\, this me
 ans that registration and the waitlist have filled for this date and time
 .Plan to arrive early to check in. At 1:25 p.m.\, any unclaimed spaces ma
 y be released to guests who are standing by waiting for a space.Admission
  and tours are free.A small handbag may be carried at your side. Larger b
 ags and backpacks will need to be stored before touring.Read about where 
 to find us\, where to park\, accessibility\, and museum guidelines.When Y
 ou ArriveCheck in with Guest Services staff on the first floor.If you par
 k in the IMU parking lot\, Guest Services can validate your parking vouch
 er for a discount.Be sure to store backpacks and large bags before tourin
 g. Lockers and coat racks are available.Keep space (18") between yourself
 \, including anything you're carrying\, and the art.
