SUMMARY:DIY Metal Pour Workshop
DESCRIPTION:During this workshop\, attendees will learn about the Sculptu
 re Trails Outdoor Museum\, see examples of lost-wax and relief sculptures
  in the Eskenazi Museum of Art's collection\, and will be walked through 
 how to carve a relief sculpture on a provided "scratch block." Leading th
 e carving workshop are Sculpture Trails Outdoor Museum staff Laura Gonzal
 ez (Outreach Coordinator) and Ethan Harmon (Artist-in-Residence)\, as wel
 l as Eskenazi Museum of Art's resident Arts-based Wellness Experiences Ma
 nager\, Keaton Evans-Black.PLEASE NOTE: Your scratch block will be taken 
 to the Sculpture Trails Outdoor Museum to be completed through their meta
 l pour process. During the workshop\, you must schedule to retrieve your 
 artwork from either the Eskenazi Museum of Art or the Sculpture Trails Ou
 tdoor Museum at a later date.For more information about the Sculpture Tra
 ils Outdoor Museum\, click here. (https://sculpturetrails.com/about/)
