 work in the studio\, reflecting on the theme of "What America Means to Me
 ."</p><p><strong>Know Before You Go:</strong></p><p>  Meet us on the 1st 
 floor of the museum at 10 a.m. Together\, we'll drop off personal items i
 n the Simpson Center for Education before exploring the galleries. After 
 seeing artworks that will inspire our project\, we'll head back to the Ro
 ehm Family Art-Making Studio to create our own masterpieces! Don't forget
  to dress for a mess!</p><p>  Strollers are welcome. Chaperones required.
  We ask that chaperones be 18 or older\, with one adult for every 6 child
 ren.</p><p><strong>Parking Information:</strong></p><p>  The museum is in
