 rapher <strong>Rania Matar</strong> (b. 1964\, Lebanon)\, whose striking 
 portraits document young women persisting in uncertain times. Matar's len
 s highlights women's creativity\, strength\, dignity\, and resilienceŌĆöo
 ffering a powerful counter-narrative to the challenges of her country and
  region. <a href="https://artmuseum.indiana.edu/exhibitions/upcoming/_fea
 ture-exhibitions/2026-03-05-rania-matar-where-do-i-go.html">Read more abo
 ut this featured exhibition</a>.</p><p>  Join us for a rare opportunity t
 o explore the artist's work in depth\, guided by the scholar who research
